cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image annotation tasks. It also involves the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a modification to the existing CNN-RNN design pattern, which involves training the models jointly, suggesting that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments on image captioning, which is a sub-field of Multimedia (cs.MM), making it a possible sub-category as well.
